cs.SI, cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.DC 

The paper discusses the use of entropy statistics to analyze changes in citation patterns among journals, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries) are likely because they deal with the analysis of large-scale networks and information retrieval, which are relevant to the study of citation patterns. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also relevant because it deals with the organization and retrieval of information, which is related to the organization of the sciences. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are less likely but still possible because they deal with statistical analysis and large-scale data processing, which are relevant to the methods used in the paper.
